                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Moga, May 8 (PTI): A taxi driver allegedly raped a woman yesterday at a deserted place in Punjabs Moga district after giving her an intoxicant-laced cola drink.           
	The woman was waiting for a bus when the driver offered to drop her at her destination free of charge. The woman was returning from a visit to a gurdwara in Ludhiana. When the cab reached Ajitwal, the driver stopped the vehicle and offered her the drink. Later, when she became unconscious, the driver drove her to an isolated place and raped her.                   
	 Coimbatore (PTI): Tamil Nadu tops all states in detection and recovery of stolen property. The detection rate in Tamil Nadu stands at 91 per cent and the recovery rate at 85 per cent, a top state police officer has claimed .                   
	 Bulandshahr (PTI): Bollywood playback singer Sunidhi Chauhans grandmother has filed a complaint with the Uttar Pradesh police saying she had received a phone call demanding Rs 50,000 and threatening her with dire consequences if she failed to pay up.                                                                                                                                              
